-- ‚îÄ‚îÄ Content at Scale ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Content at Scale (contentatscale.ai) is an AI content generation platform focused on producing long-form, SEO-optimized blog articles designed to read as human-written and pass AI-content detectors. Founded in 2022 by Justin McGill, the parent brand rebranded to BrandWell in 2024 while continuing to operate its flagship AI writing product, now centered on a tool called RankWell, under the contentatscale.ai domain. It targets marketing teams, agencies, and publishers producing large volumes of research-backed articles.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription, billed monthly, plus a low-cost short-term trial$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$$15 for a 7-day trial; ongoing plans from around $249/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2022, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Small to mid-size startup; exact headcount not publicly disclosed$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$United States; exact city not publicly disclosed$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Content at Scale Review 2026: Pricing, RankWell AI Writer$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Content at Scale (RankWell by BrandWell) generates long-form SEO articles with AI. See pricing, features, pros, cons and FAQs for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Content at Scale is an AI-powered content generation platform built to produce long-form, search-engine-optimized blog articles with minimal manual writing effort. It was founded in September 2022 by Justin McGill, who had previously built the sales-lead-generation company LeadFuze, and the product quickly became known in the SEO and content marketing community for its emphasis on generating articles that read as naturally human-written and are built to withstand AI-content-detection tools, at a time when the market was flooded with generic AI writing tools following the rise of ChatGPT. In August 2024, the parent company announced a rebrand from Content at Scale to BrandWell, reflecting an expansion beyond pure content generation into a broader set of brand-growth capabilities, including audience and intent data tools; existing customers were migrated to BrandWell plans at no price increase. Despite that corporate rebrand, the original contentatscale.ai domain and Content at Scale name continue to operate as a live product, now centered on a feature called RankWell, described as an all-in-one SEO AI writer, alongside a companion capability called WriteWell that generates the article text from RankWell's research output. The core workflow starts from a keyword, a URL, a podcast episode, or a video, from which the system performs automated research, analyzing top-ranking Google results, keyword and topical-cluster data, and other real-time signals, before producing a long-form article, commonly in the 1,000 to 7,000-plus word range, complete with an SEO title, meta description, header structure, table of contents, and an FAQ section, generally within minutes. The platform states it uses a multi-model AI stack, drawing on more than one large language model, to improve originality and reduce detectability as AI-generated text, and it includes SEO tooling such as keyword and topic research, content briefs, and optimization audits for both new and existing pages. It also offers native WordPress publishing with Yoast and RankMath compatibility, along with free standalone tools such as an AI content detector and a plagiarism checker that function as lead generators for the paid product. Content at Scale, under BrandWell, also markets an agency-focused tier with white-label options and multi-site support, targeting three main audience segments: in-house marketing teams and executives who need consistent output without hiring more writers, agencies and freelance writers producing content for multiple clients, and large publishers who monetize traffic through advertising or affiliate programs and need to scale article output economically. Pricing is subscription-based rather than pure pay-per-word: a low-cost 7-day trial is available for fifteen dollars and includes one fully optimized article, while ongoing plans have been publicly listed in the range of roughly 249 dollars per month for an Essentials tier, covering one user, a small number of sites, and around 25 SEO-optimized article credits per month, up to around 499 dollars per month for an Agency tier that adds a second user, multiple client sites, white-label access, and unlimited AI agents and audits. Because pricing, plan names, and even the parent brand have changed multiple times since 2022, prospective buyers should verify current plan details directly on contentatscale.ai or brandwell.ai before purchasing, since older reviews and comparison articles may reference discontinued plan names or price points.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '6f8e138d-a5e5-4a77-8e06-6e2cb41eb180';

