-- ‚îÄ‚îÄ ContentBot ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$ContentBot (ContentBot.ai) is an AI writing and content-automation platform that generates blog posts, ad copy, product descriptions, and other marketing text using large language models such as GPT-4. Founded in early 2021 and based in Miami, Florida, it offers both subscription plans and pay-as-you-go word credits, along with workflow automation that chains multiple AI writing steps together. It is used mainly by solo marketers, bloggers, copywriters, and small agencies producing content at volume.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription plus pay-as-you-go word credits$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$From $9/month for the Starter plan (50,000 words/month), or $0.50 per 1,000 words prepaid$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2021, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Small; exact headcount not publicly disclosed$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Miami, Florida, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$ContentBot Review 2026: Pricing, Features, Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$ContentBot.ai is an AI writing and workflow automation tool for blogs, ads and product copy. Compare pricing plans, features, pros, cons and FAQs.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$ContentBot, marketed at ContentBot.ai, is an AI content generation and automation platform aimed at marketers, bloggers, copywriters, and small agencies that need to produce written content, such as blog posts, ad copy, and product descriptions, without hiring additional writers. The company has been operating since early 2021, is headquartered in Miami, Florida, and by its own reported figures serves more than 200,000 registered marketers, with over 120,000 described as active content marketers, agencies, founders, and copywriters. ContentBot's primary AI writing engine has been built around OpenAI's GPT-4 model, and the platform states that a large majority of the content it generates is unique rather than directly copied from existing sources. Beyond a standard AI writing interface, ContentBot's differentiating feature is its AI Workflow Builder, which lets users chain together multiple AI generation and editing steps, for example generating a blog outline, expanding it into a draft, adjusting tone, and running a plagiarism check, into a single repeatable automation rather than running each step manually. Other core tools include an AI Blog Writer on its fourth major version, an AI chat interface, blog outline and topic idea generators, a rewriter and tone-changer, a bullet-point expander, an import tool for bulk content generation from spreadsheets, and a built-in plagiarism checker that flags overlapping content and its source. ContentBot supports content generation in roughly 110 languages, making it usable outside English-only markets. Pricing follows a hybrid model: a prepaid, pay-as-you-go option charges $0.50 per 1,000 words with volume ranging from 15,000 up to 5 million words per purchase and includes 10,000 free words on a user's first purchase, while subscription plans include a Starter tier at $9 per month for 50,000 words, a Premium tier at $29 per month for 150,000 words with up to three AI workflows and CSV imports capped at 50 rows, and a Premium+ tier at $49 per month for 400,000 words with unlimited AI workflows and imports up to 500 rows. All subscription tiers include unlimited team seats, meaning a single plan can be shared across a whole team without per-seat charges, which is somewhat unusual compared with competitors that charge per user. ContentBot is positioned as a budget-friendly alternative to larger AI writing platforms like Jasper or Copy.ai, trading some of the polish and enterprise features of those tools for substantially lower price points and a workflow-automation angle aimed at people who want to template and repeat their content-generation process rather than write prompts from scratch every time. It is best suited to individual creators, small content teams, and agencies producing high volumes of relatively short- to medium-length marketing copy, and less suited to enterprise teams needing advanced brand-voice governance, formal compliance documentation, or deep CMS integrations, none of which are prominently featured in its public materials.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
