-- ‚îÄ‚îÄ ContentKing ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$ContentKing was a real-time technical SEO monitoring and auditing platform, founded in 2015 in Amsterdam, that continuously crawled websites to alert teams to SEO-breaking changes such as accidental noindex tags, broken redirects, or removed canonical tags. It was acquired by SEO platform Conductor in February 2022 and has since been fully absorbed into Conductor's product suite, now operating under the name Conductor Monitoring. As of 2025, ContentKing is no longer sold as a standalone product; its capabilities are only available as part of a Conductor platform subscription.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Formerly a standalone SaaS subscription; now bundled into Conductor's platform with custom enterprise pricing$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Not available standalone; Conductor platform pricing is custom and quote-based$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2015, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Not applicable as a standalone company; now part of Conductor, which has several hundred employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Originally Amsterdam, Netherlands; now operates as part of Conductor, headquartered in New York City, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$ContentKing in 2026: Now Conductor Monitoring, Explained$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$ContentKing was acquired by Conductor and is no longer standalone. Learn what it did, its history, and where its real-time SEO monitoring lives today.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$ContentKing was a real-time technical SEO monitoring and auditing platform founded in 2015 in Amsterdam, the Netherlands, by Vincent van Scherpenseel alongside a co-founder. Unlike traditional SEO crawlers that audit a site on a scheduled or on-demand basis, ContentKing's core differentiator was continuous, always-on monitoring: it maintained a persistent crawl of a customer's website and flagged SEO-relevant changes, such as a page accidentally being set to noindex, a canonical tag being removed or altered, a redirect chain breaking, a title tag changing, or a page returning a server error, in near real time, often within minutes of the change occurring, rather than waiting for the next scheduled crawl to surface the problem. This was particularly valuable for large, frequently updated websites and for enterprise teams where an accidental deployment or CMS change could silently hurt search rankings for days before being noticed. ContentKing raised early seed funding, around 350,000 euros in a 2018 round, and grew to serve roughly 200 enterprise-level customers, including well-known brands such as Netflix, Adidas, and H and M, out of about 775 total customers, before being acquired by Conductor, an enterprise SEO and content marketing platform founded in 2006 and headquartered in New York City, in February 2022. The acquisition was funded in part by a prior 150 million dollar investment Conductor received from Bregal Sagemount, and the deal integrated ContentKing's real-time monitoring technology directly into Conductor's broader organic marketing platform rather than operating it as a fully separate acquired brand indefinitely. For a period after the acquisition, ContentKing continued to be sold and used somewhat independently, including gaining single sign-on integration with the main Conductor platform. However, starting in the summer of 2025, Conductor fully rolled ContentKing into its core product suite under the name Conductor Monitoring, also referred to in places as Conductor Website Monitoring, and it is no longer possible to purchase or subscribe to ContentKing as a standalone tool; the original contentkingapp.com domain now redirects visitors directly to Conductor's website. This means that, as of 2026, anyone wanting ContentKing's original real-time monitoring capability must sign up for the full Conductor enterprise platform, which bundles monitoring together with Conductor's other organic search, content intelligence, and AI-search-visibility tools, at custom, quote-based enterprise pricing rather than the smaller-team-friendly pricing ContentKing offered as an independent product. Historically, ContentKing's standalone plans were positioned for a range of site sizes, but current published estimates suggest comparable enterprise-tier monitoring inside Conductor's platform can start in the range of several thousand dollars per year, though exact figures are not publicly listed and require a sales conversation. For anyone evaluating options today, it is important to understand that ContentKing is best understood as a legacy product name: reviewers, comparison sites, and directories referencing ContentKing in 2026 are effectively describing a feature set that now lives inside Conductor, and businesses looking for a smaller, standalone real-time SEO monitoring tool at a lower price point typically compare alternatives such as Sitebulb Cloud or Lumar instead.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '8d187108-39b3-4079-8b9b-01b74263686b';

