-- ‚îÄ‚îÄ ContentShake AI ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$ContentShake AI is an AI-powered content writing tool built by Semrush that combines generative AI with Semrush's SEO data, including keyword research, competitor analysis, and search intent, to help users research, draft, and optimize articles in one workflow. Launched in April 2023, it has since been folded into Semrush's broader Content Toolkit branding, though the ContentShake name is still widely used in marketing and reviews. Semrush itself became part of Adobe following an acquisition completed in April 2026.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Subscription, either as a standalone add-on or bundled into Semrush's core plans$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$From about $60/month standalone, or included starting with Semrush's Pro plan from around $139/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2023, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Built by Semrush, which had roughly 2,000 to 2,300 employees before becoming part of Adobe in April 2026$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Boston, Massachusetts, United States (Semrush's original headquarters; Semrush is now part of Adobe)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$ContentShake AI Review 2026: Semrush's AI Writer, Pricing$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$ContentShake AI is Semrush's AI writing tool that blends SEO data with content generation. See pricing, features, pros, cons and FAQs for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$ContentShake AI is an AI-assisted content writing product built by Semrush, the SEO and digital marketing platform originally headquartered in Boston, Massachusetts. Semrush launched ContentShake AI in April 2023 as a lighter-weight, more accessible alternative to its existing, more complex SEO content tools, aimed specifically at small marketing teams, solo bloggers, and content creators who wanted AI drafting assistance directly informed by real search data rather than a generic large-language-model wrapper with no SEO context. The product's core workflow starts with a Topic Finder tool that recommends article topics using live Semrush data such as search volume, keyword difficulty, and search intent, so content ideas are grounded in demonstrated search demand rather than guesswork. From a chosen topic or target keyword, ContentShake AI can generate a full draft article, provide an on-page SEO content score comparing the draft against top-ranking competitor pages, and suggest edits to improve topical coverage, structure, and keyword usage. It supports two broad article types: standard AI-generated articles based on a keyword, available in effectively unlimited quantity on paid plans, and SEO-boosted articles that undergo deeper competitive research and optimization, which are metered and limited per plan. The tool includes a built-in WordPress integration for one-click publishing, so a finished draft can be pushed live without manually copying content into a CMS. Over time, Semrush folded ContentShake AI into a broader umbrella it calls the Content Toolkit, which bundles content ideation, writing, optimization, and repurposing tools, including for surfaces beyond traditional search such as content built to be cited by AI search engines, under one banner; industry commentary treats this as a rebrand and consolidation rather than a discontinuation of ContentShake's underlying functionality, and the ContentShake name is still commonly used in marketing materials, documentation, and third-party reviews as of 2026. Pricing works two ways: ContentShake AI or Content Toolkit access can be purchased as a roughly $60 per month standalone subscription that includes a set number of SEO-boosted articles per month, around five, plus unlimited standard articles, with additional SEO-boosted article packs, for example ten extra articles, purchasable for roughly $30; alternatively, the toolkit is included as part of Semrush's core subscription tiers, which have started around $139 per month for the Pro plan and scale up through Guru, around $249 per month, and Business, around $499 per month, tiers that add more users, higher usage limits, and additional Semrush features unrelated to content writing. A significant company-level change occurred in 2026: Adobe completed an approximately 1.9 billion dollar all-cash acquisition of Semrush Holdings in April 2026, meaning Semrush, and by extension ContentShake AI, now operates as part of Adobe's customer-experience and marketing portfolio rather than as an independently publicly traded company. ContentShake AI is best suited to marketers and businesses already using or open to using the Semrush ecosystem, since its main advantage over generic AI writers is the tight coupling with Semrush's keyword, competitor, and SERP data; users who only want a standalone writing assistant without an SEO data layer may find dedicated writing tools cheaper or simpler.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '82e40996-2042-4195-bace-52a95dd90735';

